rived from <i>īd</i> ‘work’. This died out during the later Middle Ages. It was revived in the 19th century, influenced by its use in  Tennyson's  The Princess (  1847 ) for the central character, who devotes herself to the cause of women's rights and women's education in a thoroughly Victorian way. The name is also associated with Mount Ida in Crete, which was connected in classical times with the worship of Zeus, king of the gods, who was supposed to have been brought up in a cave on the mountainside. In the 1930s it became famous as the name of the film star  Ida Lupino  (  1914–1995 )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Ida was born about 1250. She married Alexander Bozum about 1270, in Roxton, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"about 1250–":"umbes 1250–Surnud","1250–1298":"1250–1298","1274–1330":"1274–1330","1250–Female":"1250–Surnud","about 1250":"umbes 1250","about 1272":"1274","about 1270":"umbes 1270","1298":"1298","1330":"1330","1274":"1274","1250":"1250","Roxton, Bedfordshire, England":"Roxton, Bedfordshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1250–":"noin 1250–Kuollut","1250–1298":"1250–1298","1274–1330":"1274–1330","1250–Female":"1250–Kuollut","about 1250":"noin 1250","about 1272":"1274","about 1270":"noin 1270","1298":"1298","1330":"1330","1274":"1274","1250":"1250","Roxton, Bedfordshire, England":"Roxton, Bedfordshire, England"},"fr":{"about 1250–":"environ 1250–Décédée","1250–1298":"1250–1298","1274–1330":"1274–1330","1250–Female":"1250–Décédée","about 1250":"environ 1250","about 1272":"1274","about 1270":"environ 1270","1298":"1298","1330":"1330","1274":"1274","1250":"1250","Roxton, Bedfordshire, England":"Roxton, Bedfordshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Ida est née environ 1250. Elle a épousé Alexander Bozum environ 1270, à Roxton, Bedfordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"about 1250–":"um 1250–Verstorben","1250–1298":"1250–1298","1274–1330":"1274–1330","1250–Female":"1250–Ver